1
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:06,040
这里，或许就是印度版的樟宜机场。
This might just be India's answer to Changi.

2
00:00:07,279 --> 00:00:10,297
它叫纳维孟买国际机场，
It's called Navim Mumbai International Airport

3
00:00:10,297 --> 00:00:14,496
去年12月已正式对旅客开放航站楼。
and it opened its terminals to passengers in December last year.

4
00:00:14,496 --> 00:00:18,204
整个机场看起来相当惊艳，而这仅仅是第一阶段。
The place looks pretty stunning and that's just phase 1.

5
00:00:18,204 --> 00:00:20,389
等到最终阶段完工，
Once the final phase is complete,

6
00:00:20,388 --> 00:00:24,890
纳维孟买每年将迎来多达9000万名旅客，
Navi Mumbai will welcome an astounding 90 million passengers a year,

7
00:00:24,890 --> 00:00:26,744
比樟宜机场还多出2000万。
20 million more than Changi.

8
00:00:26,744 --> 00:00:30,800
印度希望这里能成为全球航空枢纽。
India wants this to become a hub for world travel.

9
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:33,034
当然，任何人听到有新机场敢跟新加坡的骄傲相提并论，对此持怀疑态度
Now, you'd be right to raise an eyebrow

10
00:00:33,034 --> 00:00:36,348
也完全情有可原。
to any newcomer being compared to Singapore's Pride and Joy.

11
00:00:36,348 --> 00:00:39,760
樟宜可以说是世界上最好的机场。
That is arguably the best airport in the world.

12
00:00:40,399 --> 00:00:44,162
不过别忘了，樟宜在成为民用机场之前，很长一段时间只是个军用空军基地。
But don't forget that Changi was a military air base

13
00:00:44,162 --> 00:00:47,201
纳维孟买的工程师们压根儿没有在空军基地上建机场的机会——
long before it became a civilian facility.

14
00:00:47,201 --> 00:00:50,747
他们面对的现实截然不同。
The engineers behind Navi Mumbai could only dream

15
00:00:50,747 --> 00:00:55,450
他们面对的现实截然不同。
of building on an air base. Their reality was entirely different.

16
00:00:55,451 --> 00:01:00,447
他们的任务，是在一片布满不稳定滩涂的沼泽地上
They were tasked with building an airport on a swamp covered in unstable mud flats,

17
00:01:00,447 --> 00:01:01,229
建造一座机场——这片地里还有一座大山，
a giant hill,

18
00:01:01,229 --> 00:01:04,299
以及一条从中间穿过的河流。
and a river flowing right through the middle of it.

19
00:01:04,299 --> 00:01:08,183
纳维孟买国际机场的效果图看起来无比震撼，
While the renders of Navi Mumbai International look spectacular,

20
00:01:08,183 --> 00:01:11,520
但这座机场的选址，简直就是一场噩梦。
this airport's location has been an absolute nightmare.

21
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:19,339
印度拥有全球增速最快的航空市场之一，
India has one of the fastest growing aviation sectors on the planet

22
00:01:19,339 --> 00:01:21,200
仅次于中国和美国。
behind only China and the US.

23
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:26,108
在总理纳伦德拉·莫迪大力推进印度交通基础设施升级的背景下，
The number of operational airports in the country has doubled in the last decade

24
00:01:26,108 --> 00:01:30,590
全国在用机场数量在过去十年里翻了一番。
as Prime Minister Narendra Modi looks set to overhaul India's travel infrastructure.

25
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:34,498
然而，作为印度金融中心的孟买，配套资源却严重不足。
Mumbai, its financial powerhouse is under resourced.

26
00:01:34,498 --> 00:01:39,294
世界上许多知名大城市都拥有多座主要机场——
A number of the world's most prominent cities feature multiple major airports.

27
00:01:39,294 --> 00:01:41,262
伦敦、纽约、东京，莫不如此。
Think London, New York or Tokyo.

28
00:01:41,263 --> 00:01:45,636
这对入境旅客数量、商务出行以及货运来说，显然都至关重要。
And that's obviously crucial for visitor numbers, business trips and cargo.

29
00:01:45,635 --> 00:01:47,345
就拿伦敦来说吧。
Let's take London for example.

30
00:01:47,346 --> 00:02:01,680
伦敦有六座主要机场，2024年合计接待了高达1.77亿名旅客。而孟买历史上一直只有一座主要机场。
The city is serviced by six major airports. All of those combined handled a whopping 177 million passengers in 2024. Mumbai, however, has historically had just one major airport.

31
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:08,801
这就好比伦敦只有希思罗一座机场——每年白白错过近1亿旅客。
That would be like London having just Heathrow. The city would miss out on nearly 100 million passengers every year.

32
00:02:08,801 --> 00:02:12,410
考虑到印度航空市场的快速增长，
And given that rapidly growing aviation sector in India,

33
00:02:12,410 --> 00:02:16,921
这个国家迫切需要提升金融首都的航空承载能力。
the country is desperate to improve capacity to its financial capital.

34
00:02:16,921 --> 00:02:20,710
当局给出的答案听起来很简单——
The answer authorities came up with was simple.

35
00:02:20,711 --> 00:02:23,644
在孟买再建一座主要机场。
a second major airport in Mumbai.

36
00:02:23,643 --> 00:02:25,857
但把这种规模的想法落地，远没有灵光乍现那一刻来得轻松。
But executing an idea of this scale

37
00:02:25,857 --> 00:02:33,510
孟买第二大机场计划面临的最大难题，
is rarely as straightforward as having the epiphany itself. The biggest problem faced by Mumbai's second big airport plan

38
00:02:33,509 --> 00:02:38,000
是大城市普遍存在的共同困境：空间不足。
is experienced by major cities all around the world. The lack of space.

39
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:42,276
看看现在的孟买机场，已经处于满负荷状态。
Just take a look at Mumbai airport which is already at capacity.

40
00:02:42,276 --> 00:02:45,251
这边的一号航站楼正在翻新改造，
Terminal one over here is going through a redevelopment,

41
00:02:45,251 --> 00:02:48,863
但扩大占地面积的空间实在有限。
but there isn't exactly a lot of scope for expanding the footprints.

42
00:02:48,862 --> 00:02:51,724
四面八方都是密集的居民区，
On every side, there are densely packed communities

43
00:02:51,724 --> 00:02:53,632
搬迁难度极大——
that would be a nightmare to move,

44
00:02:53,631 --> 00:02:55,539
当然，他们也不是没尝试过。
and it's not like they didn't try.

45
00:02:55,539 --> 00:02:58,420
二号航站楼就是最好的证据。
That evidence can be found over at Terminal 2.

46
00:02:58,420 --> 00:03:00,794
这里的候机廊是不对称的。
The concourses here are asymmetrical.

47
00:03:00,794 --> 00:03:03,353
最初的规划是两边等长，
The initial plan was for them to be the same length,

48
00:03:03,353 --> 00:03:07,388
但由于在迁移机场边界社区时遭遇重重阻力，
but because of the challenges faced in moving communities on the airport boundary,

49
00:03:07,388 --> 00:03:09,455
第二条候机廊不得不重新设计。
the second concourse had to be redesigned.

50
00:03:09,454 --> 00:03:11,299
看起来像是被截断了——
It looks like it's been cut off

51
00:03:11,299 --> 00:03:15,167
这自然也限制了可用登机口的数量。
and that obviously limits the number of gates that are available.

52
00:03:15,168 --> 00:03:19,371
另外，由于跑道相互交叉，飞机起降也受到严格限制。
Air traffic is also pretty restricted because of the intersecting runways.

53
00:03:19,371 --> 00:03:21,951
现有设计导致两条跑道无法同时起降飞机。
The design stops planes landing and taking off

54
00:03:21,951 --> 00:03:23,689
现有设计导致两条跑道无法同时起降飞机。
on each strip at the same time.

55
00:03:23,689 --> 00:03:24,747
而且正如我们之前提到的，
And as we pointed out,

56
00:03:24,747 --> 00:03:28,258
附近根本没有空间再建平行跑道。
it's not like there's a lot of space to build parallel runways elsewhere.

57
00:03:28,258 --> 00:03:34,713
结果就是，孟买每年白白流失数百万旅客和大量货物，
The result is that Mumbai is missing out on potentially millions of passengers and tons of cargo every year,

58
00:03:34,713 --> 00:03:38,120
这座城市的核心机场真的已经到了亟需援助的地步。
and the city's key airport really is crying out for help.

59
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:41,354
但显然，大规模扩建是行不通的，
But clearly a major expansion is out of the question,

60
00:03:41,354 --> 00:03:45,686
在市中心附近新建一座大型机场也同样不现实。
as is constructing a massive new airport anywhere near the city center.

61
00:03:45,685 --> 00:03:47,102
那出路在哪里？
So where do you go?

62
00:03:47,102 --> 00:03:52,628
经过长达10年的选址，再加上3年的土地收购，
Well, after a 10year search and then a further 3 years spent buying up land,

63
00:03:52,628 --> 00:03:54,373
当局最终相中了这里——距离孟买老商业中心约40公里的纳维孟买。
officials ended up here.

64
00:03:54,373 --> 00:04:00,480
当局最终相中了这里——距离孟买老商业中心约40公里的纳维孟买。
It's about 40 km away from the old commercial center of Mumbai over in Nav'i Mumbai.

65
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:03,432
顺应近十年来的流行趋势，
In what's become a growing trend over the last decade,

66
00:04:03,432 --> 00:04:06,197
纳维孟买国际机场选址于海岸边。
the Nav'i Mumbai international site is on the coast.

67
00:04:06,197 --> 00:04:09,320
这意味着机场主要建在填海造地的土地上，
That means it's built largely on reclaimed land

68
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:12,045
前期准备工作量极为庞大。
and that's required a lot of preparation.

69
00:04:12,045 --> 00:04:14,869
好了，在今天的视频继续深入之前，
Now, before we go any further with today's video,

70
00:04:14,869 --> 00:04:16,368
我必须先暂停一下——
we need to stop everything

71
00:04:16,368 --> 00:04:20,576
因为我有一个超级重大的消息，终于可以公开了！
because I have got some very big news that I am finally allowed to share.

72
00:04:20,576 --> 00:04:24,898
去年，企鹅兰登书屋问我有没有兴趣写一本书，
Last year, Penguin Random House asked me if I'd like to write a book.

73
00:04:24,898 --> 00:04:25,587
我答应了。
I said yes.

74
00:04:25,587 --> 00:04:28,305
书已经写完了，就是这本！
I've written a book and here it is.

75
00:04:28,385 --> 00:04:34,075
书名叫《超级工程：改变世界的10大超级建造项目》（Mega Builds: 10 Colossal Construction Projects That Will Change World）。
It is called Mega Builds: 10 Colossal Construction Projects That Will Change World.

76
00:04:34,076 --> 00:04:35,347
过去10年，
Over the last 10 years,

77
00:04:35,347 --> 00:04:40,375
我有幸近距离见证了地球上一些最令人叹为观止的建设项目，
I have had a front row seat to some of this planet's most incredible construction projects,

78
00:04:40,375 --> 00:04:41,756
它们全都收录在这本书里。
and they are all in here.

79
00:04:41,755 --> 00:04:45,607
我把这些故事写了下来，深入程度
I've written about them. I've gone deeper than I've ever gone before

80
00:04:45,607 --> 00:04:49,120
远超我过去做过的任何视频、任何长纪录片。
in any video story or any kind of like long- form documentary.

81
00:04:49,199 --> 00:04:50,708
这是幕后故事。
This is behind the scenes.

82
00:04:50,708 --> 00:04:53,257
是近距离接触、是与团队的面对面交流。
It's up close and personal. It meets the teams.

83
00:04:53,257 --> 00:04:54,332
是人物背后的故事。
It's the human stories.

84
00:04:54,332 --> 00:04:55,895
是工程技术的细节拆解。
It's the engineering in detail.

85
00:04:55,895 --> 00:04:58,434
也是我的亲身经历，以及那些在近距离接触这些项目过程中闹出的各种糗事。
It's my personal experiences and some of the calamities

86
00:04:58,434 --> 00:05:02,866
写这本书我真的享受其中。
I've had along the way getting up close with these projects. I have really enjoyed writing this.

87
00:05:02,866 --> 00:05:04,985
我的一些朋友听说后，冒出了这样一句话："哦，不错嘛，
Some of my mates have been like, "Oh, nice.

88
00:05:04,985 --> 00:05:07,808
那……那谁帮你代笔的？"没有人代笔。
Who uh who ghost wrote that for you?" No one.

89
00:05:07,808 --> 00:05:10,047
我请不起什么大牌代笔作家。是我自己写的。
I can't afford a fancy ghost writer. Me.

90
00:05:10,047 --> 00:05:13,666
每一个字都是从我脑子里
I wrote this. Every single word of this has come from my head

91
00:05:13,666 --> 00:05:15,980
蹦出来，敲进电脑，最后印进这本书的。
into my laptop and then into this book.

92
00:05:15,980 --> 00:05:17,852
全都是为了让你们读得尽兴。
All for your reading pleasure.

93
00:05:17,852 --> 00:05:19,909
说真的，我从来没想过自己能写一本书——但我做到了。
Guys, I never thought I could write a book, but I have.

94
00:05:19,909 --> 00:05:22,827
当然我可能有点自吹自擂，但说实话，我自己读完觉得还挺不错的。
And obviously, I'm biased, but I actually kind of think it's quite good.

95
00:05:22,827 --> 00:05:26,160
现在已经开放预购，链接在下方。
It is available to pre-order now. The link is below.

96
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:28,080
预购真的非常非常重要。
Pre-ordering is incredibly important.

97
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:32,080
说白了，我今后的幸福全靠你们预购这本书了。
Basically, my entire future happiness depends on you pre-ordering this book.

98
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:34,828
所以各位，如果你喜欢B1M频道，喜欢这些故事，
So guys, if you love the B1M, if you love these stories,

99
00:05:34,828 --> 00:05:38,484
如果你喜欢用深入浅出、通俗易懂
if you love learning more about construction in a downto-earth way

100
00:05:38,484 --> 00:05:41,364
的方式了解建筑工程，
that's easy to understand and can be read by anyone,

101
00:05:41,364 --> 00:05:43,856
那就去预购我的书《超级工程》（Mega Builds）吧！
go and pre-order my book, Mega Builds, today.

102
00:05:43,855 --> 00:05:47,895
在2018年正式动工
Before any work could start on the foundations back in 2018,

103
00:05:47,895 --> 00:05:50,319
打地基之前，有三道关键难关必须先行攻克，
three key hurdles had to be tackled,

104
00:05:50,318 --> 00:05:52,742
每一道都相当棘手。
and each of them was pretty massive.

105
00:05:52,742 --> 00:05:55,946
分别是：山丘、沼泽地，以及一条河流。
We Hill, Swampland, and Ol River.

106
00:05:55,946 --> 00:05:57,469
先说第一个。
Let's start here.

107
00:05:57,469 --> 00:06:01,940
在新机场选址的正中央，
Right in the middle of the site for the new airport,

108
00:06:01,940 --> 00:06:06,240
有一座海拔92米的实心岩石山丘。
you'd find this all hill. It's 92 m of solid rock.

109
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:10,400
候机廊正中间矗立着一座山——显然，这一点都不理想。
Obviously, having a hill in the middle of your concourse isn't exactly ideal.

110
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:14,640
所以，在任何建设动工之前，这座山必须彻底夷平。
So, that had to be completely flattened before any building could take place.

111
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:21,453
施工队采用定向爆破的方式
Construction crews demolished 62 million cub m of rock through controlled blasting

112
00:06:21,453 --> 00:06:23,425
以保护周边村庄，共清除了6200万立方米的岩石。
to protect surrounding villages.

113
00:06:23,425 --> 00:06:26,949
但等这一切结束，工地看起来是这个样子的。
But once that was finished, the site looks like this.

114
00:06:26,949 --> 00:06:31,144
好，接下来是第二个难题——爆破出来的岩石怎么处理？
So, on to problem number two. What do you do with the blasted rock?

115
00:06:31,144 --> 00:06:36,472
答案是废物利用。原来，这座机场有数百英亩的区域建在沼泽地上。
Well, it was repurposed. You see, hundreds of acres of this airport sit on swamp land.

116
00:06:36,472 --> 00:06:38,572
这里遍布滩涂和红树林，
It's covered in mud flats and mangroves,

117
00:06:38,572 --> 00:06:43,088
所有这些都必须在施工前推平、夯实。
all of which have got to be leveled and stabilized before construction work can begin.

118
00:06:43,088 --> 00:06:46,356
为此，地基需要整体抬高约6米。
To do that, they had to raise the ground by around 6 m.

119
00:06:46,356 --> 00:06:49,737
而恰好，他们手头有海量的岩石——
And conveniently, they had enormous amounts of rock available

120
00:06:49,737 --> 00:06:52,120
就来自刚刚炸掉的那座大山。
from that big old hill they' just blown up.

121
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:57,393
真正巧妙的是，工程师们专门计算了爆破当量，
What's really cool is that these guys blasted the rock at specific explosive power designations

122
00:06:57,393 --> 00:06:58,725
让炸出的碎石粒径
to create rock fragments

123
00:06:58,725 --> 00:07:02,167
恰好符合填土开发的需求。
that were the ideal size for land development and reclamation.

124
00:07:02,167 --> 00:07:08,000
这些碎石被直接填入沼泽区域，刺穿并置换掉松软的黏土层。
The blasted rock was basically dumped into marshy areas, puncturing and displacing the soft clay.

125
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,768
岩石的重量随后将土壤压实，
The weight of all that rock then compacted the soil,

126
00:07:10,768 --> 00:07:11,726
使地基更加稳固，
making it stronger

127
00:07:11,726 --> 00:07:16,517
也减少了对软弱地基另行加固处理的工程量。
and reducing the amount of intensive treatment that was needed to thicken any weak ground.

128
00:07:16,517 --> 00:07:22,160
但挑战还没结束——这是2019年时的那条河流。
But that wasn't the final hurdle. This is River in 2019.

129
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:25,040
原本，它正好从工地中间穿过。
Originally, it cut through the middle of the site,

130
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:27,680
而一条穿越跑道的河流，除了能提供一个有趣的水景
but beyond acting as an interesting water feature,

131
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:30,848
之外，在实际工程上完全行不通。
a river through a runway is actually incredibly impractical.

132
00:07:30,848 --> 00:07:34,665
工程师别无选择，只能对河道进行改道。
Engineers were left with no choice but to redirect it.

133
00:07:34,664 --> 00:07:41,760
可以看到，河道被斜向截断，绕开了整个工地。如果你觉得河流现在看起来更宽了，没错，就是这样。
You can see it's been cut at an angle, diverting around the site. And if you're thinking it now looks bigger, then you'd be right.

134
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:47,999
纳维孟买机场周边有许多村庄，当地居民亲眼目睹了这片土地的沧桑巨变。
Navim Mumbai Airport is surrounded by villages whose people have watched this site completely transform.

135
00:07:48,319 --> 00:07:52,309
但在这些社区里，有一个非常现实的担忧——洪涝问题。
But within those communities, there's a very real concern about flooding.

136
00:07:52,309 --> 00:07:57,599
沼泽和湿地本身能通过植被和松软土壤吸收大量水分。
You see, swamp and wetlands absorb water through the vegetation and soft soil.

137
00:07:57,599 --> 00:08:03,437
但正如我们之前提到的，大面积的土地被不透水的岩石填埋，
But as we pointed out, large swades of that land have been filled in with a non-absorbent rock,

138
00:08:03,437 --> 00:08:10,996
村民们不禁担心：暴雨来临时，水往哪里跑？这也正是河道被拓宽加深的原因。
leaving villages wondering where water will run during heavy rainfall. And that's why River has been expanded and deepened.

139
00:08:10,996 --> 00:08:14,187
部分河段从原来的25米宽，
In some areas, it's grown from 25 m wide

140
00:08:14,187 --> 00:08:16,420
扩展到了令人印象深刻的200米宽。
to an impressive 200 m wide.

141
00:08:16,420 --> 00:08:18,696
工程师们希望，更宽阔的河道
The hope is that the larger area

142
00:08:18,696 --> 00:08:22,040
能在洪水期间有效蓄纳和控制过量的雨水。
is going to control excess water during floods.

143
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:27,070
在我们继续往下说之前，还记得那座必须夷平的山丘吗？
And just before we move on, remember that hill that had to be flattened? Well, that wasn't the only thing

144
00:08:27,070 --> 00:08:29,226
需要清除的可不止是这座山。
that needed taking back down to ground level.

145
00:08:29,224 --> 00:08:32,584
地面上的架空电缆也必须全部入地，
Overhead tension cables had to be rerooed underground

146
00:08:32,584 --> 00:08:35,120
以防止飞机与其相撞。
to stop airplanes from flying into them.

147
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:43,891
经过7年的建设，机场一期工程于2025年圣诞节正式开放，
Now after 7 years of construction, the first phase of the airport opened on Christmas Day 2025,

148
00:08:43,891 --> 00:08:46,558
配备了一座塔台、一条跑道、一座消防站
featuring a control tower, a single runway,

149
00:08:46,558 --> 00:08:48,480
以及一号航站楼。
a fire station, and terminal 1.

150
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:54,032
纳维孟买机场目前已可服务2000万旅客，
Already, Nav Mumbai is able to serve 20 million passengers a year,

151
00:08:54,032 --> 00:08:56,852
以及50万公吨货物。
and half a million metric tonses of cargo.

152
00:08:56,852 --> 00:09:01,440
但到2030年代第五阶段完成时，这座机场将彻底脱胎换骨。
But by the end of phase 5 in the 2030s, this airport's going to be unrecognizable.

153
00:09:01,920 --> 00:09:05,479
届时，园区将新增一条平行跑道、
The site's being enhanced with a second parallel runway,

154
00:09:05,479 --> 00:09:06,814
三座航站楼，
three more terminals,

155
00:09:06,813 --> 00:09:08,720
以及更大规模的货运设施。
and additional cargo capacity.

156
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:13,226
按照规划，纳维孟买国际机场最终将每年处理
The plans will see Navim Mumbai International eventually processing

157
00:09:13,226 --> 00:09:15,378
高达9000万旅客
a whopping 90 million passengers

158
00:09:15,378 --> 00:09:18,674
和逾300万吨货物。
and more than 3 million tons of cargo every year.

159
00:09:18,674 --> 00:09:20,959
视觉上也美得令人屏息。
And it's pretty breathtaking to look at.

160
00:09:20,959 --> 00:09:23,163
由扎哈·哈迪德建筑事务所操刀设计，
Designed by Zaha Hadid Architects,

161
00:09:23,163 --> 00:09:27,702
整体造型以印度国花——莲花为原型。
it's modeled to resemble a lotus flower, the national flower of India.

162
00:09:27,702 --> 00:09:31,599
地基采用高强度钢筋混凝土
The foundations are being developed using high strength reinforced concrete

163
00:09:31,599 --> 00:09:32,586
和预制构件，
and pre-cast panels

164
00:09:32,586 --> 00:09:34,924
以尽量加快施工进度。
to try and speed up the construction process.

165
00:09:34,924 --> 00:09:37,927
考虑到项目初期选址条件之恶劣，
The whole thing is a really impressive accomplishment

166
00:09:37,927 --> 00:09:42,176
这整套成果称得上是一项令人叹服的工程成就。
given how incredibly impractical this site was at the start of the project.

167
00:09:42,176 --> 00:09:45,679
航站楼正面，12根形如花瓣展开的柱子
At the front, 12 columns shaped like unfolding petals

168
00:09:45,679 --> 00:09:47,728
将光线引入室内，
diffuse light into the terminal

169
00:09:47,728 --> 00:09:50,240
构成一套引人注目的双层系统。
as part of a striking two-tier system.

170
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:53,677
其后方隐藏着17根巨型承重柱，
17 giant columns are then hidden behind them

171
00:09:53,677 --> 00:09:55,802
支撑着
to take the incredible weights

172
00:09:55,803 --> 00:09:57,857
那座跨度达370米的悬挑顶盖所带来的惊人荷载。
of the 370 meter canopy roof.

173
00:09:57,857 --> 00:10:01,263
弧形屋顶以钢骨架为主体，
That curved roof is created using a steel framework

174
00:10:01,263 --> 00:10:04,802
通过网状钢梁和覆层支撑，
supported by a network of steel girders and cladding.

175
00:10:04,802 --> 00:10:06,805
每一个分区都像一片花瓣，
Each section acts like a petal

176
00:10:06,805 --> 00:10:10,144
由大跨度矩形钢桁架构成。
formed using large span rectangular steel trusses.

177
00:10:10,144 --> 00:10:13,427
这些钢桁架承重能力极强，
Those trusses are able to carry a massive amount of weight

178
00:10:13,427 --> 00:10:16,880
使得室内柱子数量得以大幅减少。
and the result is the ability to reduce the number of columns

179
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:18,012
使得室内柱子数量得以大幅减少。
inside the building.

180
00:10:18,012 --> 00:10:20,837
设计目标是打造一个开阔明亮的空间，
The goal was to create a beautiful open space

181
00:10:20,837 --> 00:10:24,164
让自然光透过采光天窗倾泻而入。
with natural light flooding in through the skylights.

182
00:10:24,164 --> 00:10:26,556
我认为，这个目标可以说是完美实现了。
And I think it's fair to say mission accomplished.

183
00:10:26,556 --> 00:10:29,231
但屋顶上那些开口，
But those holes in the roof are about a lot more than

184
00:10:29,231 --> 00:10:31,705
不仅仅是为了给旅客提供美丽的视觉享受。
just giving passengers something nice to look at.

185
00:10:31,704 --> 00:10:34,860
它们实际上能收集并导流季风雨水，
They actually catch and channel monsoon rainwater

186
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:36,921
同时帮助降低风阻。
and help reduce wind resistance.

187
00:10:36,921 --> 00:10:39,703
综合来看，实用性极强。
Altogether, they're incredibly practical.

188
00:10:39,704 --> 00:10:43,198
另外，我想再回头谈一下机场的选址——
And actually, I just want to touch on the site location one more time

